			 Choose a cloud SQL Server option: Azure SQL (PaaS) Database or SQL Server on Azure VMs (IaaS) 

					 
								 02/12/2018 
							 13 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
											 
											 
										 all 
								 

					 In this article 
						 Azure has two options for hosting SQL Server workloads in Microsoft Azure: 
 Azure SQL Database : A SQL database native to the cloud, also known as a platform as a service (PaaS) database or a database as a service (DBaaS) that is optimized for software-as-a-service (SaaS) app development. It offers compatibility with most SQL Server features. For more information on PaaS, see  What is PaaS . 
